<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/2.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Chargé</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-17"><hi rend="italic">January 17,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            been instructed by His Majesty’s principal secretary of state for
                            foreign affairs to express the high appreciation of His Majesty’s
                            Government at the prompt assistance rendered by the United States
                            Government in the dispatch of their ships to Jamaica to afford aid to
                            the stricken population of Kingston.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Esme Howard.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>